                    <msContents>
                        <summary>An account, in verse, of the birth and life of the prophet
                                <persName key="person_66440309" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/66440309/"
                                >Zoroaster</persName>, by Zartusht Bahram Pazhdu, the author of
                                <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Ardāvīrāfnāmah</title> in verse and
                                <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" type="alt">Dāstān-i Jingihir
                                Nighājah</title> (see Persian MS 301). The title is given in the
                            Manuscript on folio <locus from="1v" to="1v">1v</locus> as <title
                                xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Mawlūd-i Zartusht</title>
                            <title xml:lang="fa">مولود زرتشت</title> The same is also given in the
                            text on folio <locus from="61v" to="61v">61v</locus> چو مولود زرتشت
                            خوانی تمام / بدل کن برو آفرینی تمام . The same title is also given in
                            the author’s other work, <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc">Jingihir
                                Nighājah</title>
                            <title xml:lang="fa">جنگهر نگهاچه</title> (Persian 301), where he states
                            that his mother used to read to him two works (daftar), the Mawlūd-i
                            Zartusht and the Ardā-yī vīrāf دو دفتر بود نقل اندر بر من کتابی بود زان
                            مولود زرتشت درو چیزی که بد مقصود زرتشت. The beginning of this Manuscript
                            corresponds with that in Sachau/Ethe (British Library) and to some
                            extent to that in Rieu (British Museum), but is different from that in
                            Ethe (10).</summary>
                        <msItem xml:id="Persian_MS_300-item1">
                            <author key="person_77486993" ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/77486993">
                                <persName type="standard">Zartusht Bahrām, active 1278</persName>
                                <persName xml:lang="fa">زرتشت بهرام پژدو‏</persName>
                            </author>
                            <title xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc" key="work_7038">Zartushtnāmah</title>
                            <title xml:lang="ar-Latn-x-lc" type="alt" key="work_7038">Zartusht
                                nāmah</title>
                            <title xml:lang="fa" key="work_7038">زرتشت نامه</title>
                            <incipit xml:lang="ar" type="beginning">سخن را بنام خدای جهان بآغاز
                                    <sic>بیاغاز</sic> در آشکار و نهان</incipit>
                                                      <listBibl>
                                <bibl>Modern edition by Muhammad Dablr-siyaqi (zardushj: Bahram
                                    Pazhdu, ZaratusJit- namah), Tehran 1338 (1959), For further
                                    information and translations, see Rieu, BM 46-47; Ethe, IO
                                    2819.</bibl>
                            </listBibl>
                            <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
                        </msItem>
